  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Pet Relocation Specialist",
  "description": "<p>We are building an in-house pet relocation capability and are looking for a Pet Relocation Specialist to manage animal import and export regulatory processes end to end.<br /><br />This role focuses on compliance, documentation, and coordination to ensure pets move safely and in full accordance with AVS and destination-country requirements.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Manage animal import, export and transhipment cases from intake to approval</p></li><li><p>Prepare, submit and track AVS licence applications and related regulatory documentation</p></li><li><p>Interpret AVS regulations, rabies risk categories, and country-specific requirements</p></li><li><p>Review veterinary records, vaccination histories, microchip details and health certificates</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with AVS, veterinarians, airlines, quarantine facilities and logistics partners</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate case files, timelines, SOPs and compliance checklists</p></li><li><p>Provide clear regulatory guidance to internal teams and clients</p></li><li><p>Monitor regulatory changes and update processes accordingly</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Who This Role Is For</strong></h3><ul><li><p>1–2 years of direct, hands-on experience in animal import and export regulatory approvals, licences or compliance documentation</p></li><li><p>Proven experience submitting government licence applications for animal movement</p></li><li><p>Highly organised, detail-driven, and comfortable working with formal regulatory processes</p></li><li><p>Experience with AVS, biosecurity, veterinary, logistics or regulated animal-related industries is a strong advantage</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Why Join Us</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Build a new in-house capability from the ground up</p></li><li><p>High ownership and clear responsibility from day one</p></li><li><p>Meaningful work supporting safe, compliant pet relocation</p></li><li><p>Opportunity to grow into a senior or lead role as the operation scales</p></li></ul><p><strong></strong><br />Email your resume to hello@pawpledge.co.</p>",
